wikipedia_page.main: Flight Lieutenant Forde Leathley (17 February 1896 – 25 August 1982) was an Irish First World War flying ace credited with eight aerial victories.

response: It was one of the few bomber units to produce flying aces, having five on strength. William Edward Green scored nine wins,Franks, et al, p. 66. James Grant and Forde Leathley eight,Franks, et al, p. 89. E. Graham Joy seven (plus one later in 205 Squadron),Franks, et al, p. 69. and Arthur Thomas Drinkwater scored six, all in Airco DH.4s.Franks, et al, p. 63. In total, the squadron claimed 166 German aircraft during the war, dropping 285 tons of bombs and taking 22,030 photos.
